    <abstract>
      <para>
        This guide is written for computer users who want a reference detailed 
        enough to help them to learn about Ubuntu MATE. It is written from the 
        perspective that Ubuntu MATE is a typical modern Linux for the average 
        computer user who needs to do things like browse the Internet, check 
        email, use a text editor or word processor, read and store document 
        files, view and edit photos, watch videos, listen to music, and 
        subscribe to podcasts.
      </para>
    </abstract>

