With a coffee cup for an icon, <application>Caffeine</application> is a status bar application which sits in the panel near the clock and prevents the desktop from becoming idle. Simply click on the icon and choose <guimenuitem>Activate</guimenuitem> to temporarily prevent the activation of both the screensaver and the "sleep" power saving mode. Click the icon again and choose <guimenuitem>Deactivate</guimenuitem> to go back to normal. 
          </para>
          <para>
<application>Caffeine</application> is not installed out-of-the-box with Ubuntu MATE, but it is available at no charge in the <application>Software Boutique</application> for one-click installation.
          </para>
          <informaltable frame="all">
            <tgroup cols="1">
              <colspec colwidth="100%"/>
                <tbody>
                  <row><entry><mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                      <imagedata fileref="figures/caffeine-enable.gif" contentwidth="100%"/>
                    </imageobject>
                    <textobject>
                      Using Caffeine.
                    </textobject>
                  </mediaobject></entry></row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
          </informaltable>
        </sect2> 
